# Vaccination Reminder Backend

Dual-sided hackathon app: **parents** (`/api/v1/user`) and **hospitals** (`/api/v1/hospital`).

## Roles
- `parent` — auto-provisioned on first phone JWT; profile via `PATCH /user/profile`
- `hospital` — created via `POST /hospital/signup`; owns `hospitals` row via `owner_id`

## Critical paths
- Schedules come from `hospital_vaccines`, NOT a global catalog
- Child needs `preferred_hospital_id` before schedules generate
- `parent_hospital_registrations` links parents to hospitals (`self` | `manual`)

## Stack
Express + TypeScript + Supabase (service role) + FCM + Resend + Africa's Talking (SMS stub)

## Docs
- `AGENTS.md` — agent context
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — system design
- `docs/ENVIRONMENT.md` — `.env` / platform setup
- `docs/API.md` — endpoint reference

## Code rules
- Business logic in `src/services/`, not controllers
- Throw `AppError` from services; Zod validation in routes
- Hospital queries: verify `owner_id` → `hospital_id`
- Parent queries: verify `parent_id` ownership chain
